	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				To start off bind yourself at the docks at East Freeport. Be sure to cast the required Illusion in each city as needed!<BR>
<BR>
Now hop on a boat to the Ocean of Tears and buy a Kiola Nut (just over 1 GP each) at Sister Island from the only Sister Merchant, Cleonae Kalen (Loc 500, neg 9260).<BR>
The nuts do not stack.<BR>
Gate back to the FP docks.<BR>
Note: you might get several Nuts, Honey Jum, and Erud&#8217;s Tonic&#8217;s if you are going to do the quest more than once as they are not LORE. The time to get these items is small and will save you hours later.<BR>
<BR>
Go to Misty Thicket by Rivervale.<BR>
Get 3 Honeycomb by hunting Bixies. You might advertise to buy some from a player in the zone, or look on vendors (just over 1 GP each in RV)  to save some time. The Bixies are level 1 or 2. After that, return to Rivervale and find Kizzie Mintopp (she is in a hut built into the wall near the Fools Gold, neg 230, neg 210) and give three honeycombs and 30 gp (not 3 pp) to her, and she will give you a Honey Jum.<BR>
She is a herb merchant and will call you a chatterbox when Hailed but nothing about Honey Jum. If you say &#8220;What Honey Jum?&#8221; she will tell you about it.<BR>
<BR>
Now take the boat back to North Queynos and find the Temple of Light. You will find a small pond in the center (neg 150, neg 350). Kill a Koalindl fish with a disposable Monk (because of the faction hit), loot its corpse with your main guy. If you have a slow connect get someone to make the Monk and whack the fish.<BR>
Note: Watch for the roaming guard and get the fish when he is not close or else you get to try again.<BR>
Head to Erudin.<BR>
<BR>
Buy a Innoruk's Kiss of Death (a drink) from Geoard BlueHawk (neg 1175, neg 330) at the Blue Hawk Inn. Cost is about 5 silver each. It has a Oven for baking next to the door. The Library is right next door.<BR>
Take the drink to the library (top floor) and give Sinnkin Highbrow (neg 1050, neg 250) the IKOD. She will give you the Erud's Tonic. Gate to FP.<BR>
<BR>
Go to the Seafarer's Roost on the East FP dock. Give Gregor Nasin (Bartender, neg 250, neg 830) the Honey Jum, a Kiola Nut, the Fish Corpse and the Tonic and he will give you the recipe book (Barkeeps Compendium). It is NOT required to give him all the items at once. As long as the enchanter is the one who gives the Kiola Nut after all the other ingredients were given to the barkeep, they will be given the book.<BR>
<BR>
Now head to Oggok.<BR>
Follow the path and pass the POD  and the 3 entrances (on your left) and enter the cave with 2 guards. Hang a left then another left and go past the Metil Armer &lt;sp&gt; rooms. You will end up in the Meet and Drink Tew Bie room with Chief Dooga, Clurg (250, neg 250) and Bouncer Krik.<BR>
<BR>
Now cast Alliance or Benevolence on him and give him the recipe book and you get the Stein.<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
